m studies. For the general reader, it provides a fascinating introduction to contemporary nation-building in a unique combination of cases across two continents.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Mrz 2024) 0aNation-statevCase studies. 0aNation-state. 0aNationalismzGermanyvCase studies. 0aNationalismzVietnamvCase studies. 0aNationalism. 4aInternational Relations 2019. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Ideologies / Nationalism & Patriotism.2bisacsh  aGermany.  aVietnam.  acityscapes.  acommunism.  ahistory textbooks.  amuseums.  anation-building ideology.  anational division.  anational narratives.  aregional integration.  aregionalist narratives.  asoldered states.1 aSutherland, Claire, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagez978311128363040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526135278423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526135278/original  a978-3-11-128363-0  Manchester University Press 1986 - 2013 eBook Packagec1986d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles